13:44.924 --> 13:47.518
Hey, come on out here, guys,
will you? Hurry up.

13:49.162 --> 13:50.288
- Rich...
- Yeah?

13:50.396 --> 13:51.796
Rich, you gotta go along
with this.

13:51.898 --> 13:53.593
It's the only way
you stand a chance.

13:53.700 --> 13:55.463
Ambush one guy?

13:55.568 --> 13:57.059
Three against one?

13:57.170 --> 13:59.331
Oh, I think that's worse
than the Falcons.

13:59.439 --> 14:01.202
Let's do it anyway.

14:01.307 --> 14:04.277
No, Potsie, Richie's right.
We can't do that.

14:04.377 --> 14:06.607
I'm sorry, Rich. It was my idea.

14:06.713 --> 14:08.613
You see, I was really ashamed
about the way I acted

14:08.715 --> 14:10.114
at Arnold's, you know? So...

14:10.216 --> 14:12.275
Well, Potsie and I had this talk
in homeroom.

14:12.385 --> 14:15.411
We decided we'd come here and
help you from getting creamed.

14:15.521 --> 14:16.682
Yeah.

14:16.789 --> 14:18.348
Oh.

14:18.458 --> 14:21.689
Guys, showing up,
that was really keen.

14:21.794 --> 14:25.356
Oh, well, Pots,
what can I say about you?

14:25.465 --> 14:28.298
- A lot.
-(chuckles)

14:28.401 --> 14:30.096
And, Ralph...

14:30.203 --> 14:34.037
you know, you're a real regular
guy for a... for a new kid.

14:34.140 --> 14:35.972
- Thanks, Rich.
- Yeah.

14:36.075 --> 14:38.840
But, look, guys,
I took this fight.

14:38.945 --> 14:42.438
And I-l just got to handle it
without any... ambushes.

14:42.548 --> 14:45.575
- Well, it always worked
for Randolph Scott. -Mmm.

14:45.685 --> 14:47.585
Look, Rich, are you sure
you don't want us to stay?

14:47.687 --> 14:49.246
- I'm positive.
- RALPH and POTSIE: Good!

14:49.355 --> 14:51.346
- See you later.
- Good luck.

14:53.059 --> 14:58.054
I wonder if Randolph Scott
ever cried.

15:01.868 --> 15:03.859
(sighs)

15:06.405 --> 15:08.965
10:00.

15:09.075 --> 15:11.908
I guess he's not showing up.

15:12.011 --> 15:13.809
(nervous chuckle)

15:14.947 --> 15:16.347
Heyyy.

15:18.384 --> 15:21.376
But I could be wrong.

15:24.690 --> 15:27.592
Hi.

15:27.693 --> 15:30.094
You showed.

15:30.196 --> 15:32.756
Sure, I showed. Why shouldn't
I show? I'm prompt.

15:36.769 --> 15:39.067
Very impressive.

15:39.172 --> 15:42.107
Three of my fights tonight
didn't show up.

15:42.208 --> 15:43.505
Well, that would be rude.

15:45.511 --> 15:47.741
The night wasn't a total loss.

15:47.847 --> 15:50.282
Red Devils and me had a rumble.

15:50.383 --> 15:53.045
Well, you just took
on a whole gang. Why?

15:53.152 --> 15:56.054
Because one of the Red Devils

15:56.155 --> 15:59.318
bumped into Monk on a bus.

15:59.425 --> 16:02.326
Oh, he bumped into him. Oh.

16:02.428 --> 16:04.920
What's the matter? Couldn't you
find a firing squad?

16:05.965 --> 16:08.798
We fight for a lot
of good reasons.

16:08.901 --> 16:09.959
Yeah? Like what?

16:10.069 --> 16:12.163
All right, I had
to take care of some guy

16:12.271 --> 16:14.171
because he looked
at Lefty's girl.

16:14.273 --> 16:16.674
Oh, looked at his girl.
Oh, yeah, that's a beaut.

16:16.776 --> 16:18.175
All right,
I had to take care of some guy,

16:18.277 --> 16:19.335
Big Murph, as a matter of fact,

16:19.445 --> 16:21.470
because he was down
reading our magazines

16:21.581 --> 16:23.742
at the Falcon candy store.

16:23.850 --> 16:25.579
All right, all right,
let me just get this straight.

16:25.685 --> 16:28.176
Uh, you fight for,
uh, bumping...

16:28.287 --> 16:30.187
-for looking...
- That's right.

16:30.289 --> 16:31.313
And for reading.

16:31.424 --> 16:32.391
That's right.

16:32.491 --> 16:34.050
Those are, uh...

16:34.160 --> 16:36.151
interesting reasons.

16:38.664 --> 16:40.223
They're reasons.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.164
Let's get this over with.

16:42.268 --> 16:44.168
- You ever street fight before?
- Yeah, yeah...

16:44.270 --> 16:46.170
- Tell me when.
- I've mixed it up a few times.

16:46.272 --> 16:47.899
- When?
- In the third grade once...

16:48.007 --> 16:50.499
Oh, yeah? That's what I thought.

16:50.610 --> 16:52.771
(strained):
Well, I can't remember 'em all.

16:56.816 --> 16:58.511
All right.

16:58.618 --> 17:00.677
All right, look, we came here
to fight, so let's do it.

17:00.786 --> 17:02.982
Let's just get it over with.
Will you do something?

17:03.990 --> 17:06.083
Well, what's the matter, kid?

17:06.192 --> 17:07.625
If someone punched me
in the stomach like that,

17:07.727 --> 17:09.126
I'd make him part of the wall.

17:09.228 --> 17:11.127
Okay.

17:11.230 --> 17:12.925
Okay, you asked for it.

17:13.031 --> 17:14.431
You think you're real tough,
don't you,

17:14.532 --> 17:16.694
just 'cause you got that Falcon
jacket on, don't you?

17:33.486 --> 17:35.113
Well, that answers
that question.

17:38.357 --> 17:39.848
Let's just stop dillydallying,
all right?

17:39.959 --> 17:42.951
All right, you asked for it.
You just bought it, buddy.

17:45.932 --> 17:47.900
What are you, crazy?
Bring a gun?

17:48.000 --> 17:49.559
Yeah.

17:49.669 --> 17:51.694
(imitates gunshot)

17:55.641 --> 17:57.075
So what do you want to do?

17:57.176 --> 17:59.941
You want to play
Cowboys and Indians now, huh?

18:00.046 --> 18:01.274
This time it was pretend.

18:01.380 --> 18:03.349
Next time you won't be so lucky.

18:03.449 --> 18:05.543
What happens if you run
into some dark alley?

18:05.651 --> 18:07.210
Some maniac with a real gun?

18:07.320 --> 18:09.345
Instead of a-a prompt kid
with a quick finger?

18:09.455 --> 18:11.082
Let me tell you something...

18:11.190 --> 18:13.750
Let me tell you something, punk.

18:13.859 --> 18:15.623
I knew you were kidding.

18:15.728 --> 18:17.457
I was kidding this time.

18:17.563 --> 18:20.123
What happens when somebody
finds you dead in a gutter?

18:20.232 --> 18:21.791
Because somebody bumped Monk

18:21.901 --> 18:23.801
or somebody read
a Falcon comic book?

18:23.903 --> 18:25.803
Why are you even in a gang?
It's crazy.

18:25.905 --> 18:27.270
Because I'm cool, that's why.

18:27.373 --> 18:28.932
Because there's cool in numbers,
that's why.

18:29.041 --> 18:31.135
You're cool-- I agree with that.

18:31.243 --> 18:33.610
All those other guys are cool
because of you.

18:33.713 --> 18:35.237
Did you ever think
that they're using you?

18:35.348 --> 18:38.283
Just stay off my back, all
right? Just stay off my back.

18:43.656 --> 18:45.556
You-you just...

18:45.658 --> 18:47.490
The...

18:47.593 --> 18:50.085
the whole building with the...
You just...

18:50.196 --> 18:52.028
H-How did you do that?

18:52.131 --> 18:53.929
It's a gift.

18:55.067 --> 18:57.127
Hey, you know something?
You know something?

18:57.236 --> 18:59.898
Yeah, I know something.
I did it without my jacket.

19:07.246 --> 19:08.805
Let's go.

19:08.914 --> 19:10.883
All right. But I'm warning you,

19:10.983 --> 19:13.884
I'm scrappy-

19:13.986 --> 19:16.478
Okay, scrappy-

19:16.589 --> 19:18.216
You know something, kid?

19:18.324 --> 19:19.416
You know something?

19:19.525 --> 19:21.493
You got a lot of guts.

19:21.594 --> 19:23.653
I like that.

19:23.763 --> 19:26.926
W-Was that just a-a punch?

19:27.033 --> 19:30.002
Or, uh...

19:30.102 --> 19:32.071
were you being friendly?

19:32.171 --> 19:34.230
You're still standing,
aren't you?

19:34.340 --> 19:35.534
You were being friendly.

19:35.641 --> 19:36.938
Heyyy.

19:37.043 --> 19:38.476
I'll give you a ride home.

19:38.577 --> 19:40.273
Thanks.

19:40.379 --> 19:41.904
Oh, wait a minute,
wait a minute, uh...

19:42.014 --> 19:44.142
you're forgetting something.
You...

19:44.250 --> 19:46.082
Don't forget your jacket
and your cap.

19:46.185 --> 19:47.414
Hey, what are you, crazy?

19:47.520 --> 19:49.386
You think
I need those to be cool?

19:49.488 --> 19:52.481
I think I'm gonna leave
the Falcons.

19:57.396 --> 19:58.955
Oh, so, uh...

19:59.065 --> 20:01.363
I guess what I said
kind of sunk in, huh?

20:01.467 --> 20:03.026
- Let me tell you something.
- Hmm...?

20:03.135 --> 20:05.695
I make my own decisions,
you understand?

20:05.805 --> 20:07.170
- Yeah. -I been thinking
about this a long time.

20:07.273 --> 20:08.638
I've been waiting
for the right time.

20:08.741 --> 20:10.641
You think I've got to hang
around with a bunch of nerds,

20:10.743 --> 20:13.974
bumping people, having rumbles
over stepping on somebody?

20:14.080 --> 20:17.243
Huh? You think I want to end up
in a dark alley

20:17.349 --> 20:20.376
with some prompt maniac
sticking a knife in my ribs?

20:20.486 --> 20:22.921
Whoa.

20:23.022 --> 20:25.855
Well, no, no, that's, uh...
that's good reasoning.

20:25.958 --> 20:28.052
I know that.

20:28.160 --> 20:30.789
- Let's get out of here.
- Yeah.

20:30.896 --> 20:32.626
Hold it, hold it.

20:32.731 --> 20:34.632
I never got your name.

20:34.733 --> 20:36.964
Oh, it's, uh, Cunningham.

20:37.069 --> 20:38.594
- Hmm.
- Richard Cunningham.

20:38.704 --> 20:41.674
That's cute.

20:41.774 --> 20:43.469
You can call me the Fonz.

20:43.576 --> 20:45.203
All right, uh... great.

20:45.311 --> 20:46.642
You can call me Richie.

20:46.745 --> 20:49.806
Whoa.

20:52.184 --> 20:54.175
Get out of here. Come here.

21:11.670 --> 21:13.434
So Fonzie quit the Falcons.

21:13.539 --> 21:14.973
For good.

21:15.074 --> 21:18.976
You see, he realized he didn't
have to be in a gang to be cool.

21:19.078 --> 21:21.911
Yeah, but you mean...

21:22.014 --> 21:23.175
That was the fight?

21:23.282 --> 21:25.307
Yep. That was it.

21:25.417 --> 21:28.182
Cute story, Cunningham,
but I got to run.

21:28.287 --> 21:30.278
A couple of the Lords are gonna
meet me down here.

21:30.389 --> 21:31.720
They're gonna drive me
to the rumble.

21:31.824 --> 21:33.314
What neat guys.

21:33.425 --> 21:35.894
(scoffs)

21:35.995 --> 21:37.622
I'll go load the drums.

21:37.730 --> 21:41.063
Yeah, well, thanks for listening
to my cute story.

21:47.706 --> 21:49.800
(sighs heavily)

21:49.909 --> 21:52.810
Yeah, I agree with you, Al.

21:52.912 --> 21:56.143
(both sigh heavily)

21:56.248 --> 21:58.911
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

22:01.153 --> 22:02.712
Wh-Where is he? Where is he?

22:02.821 --> 22:04.585
Do you know what that
knucklehead is doing? Huh?

22:04.690 --> 22:05.919
Where's Chachi?
He wants to join the Lords

22:06.025 --> 22:06.855
or something like that.

22:06.959 --> 22:07.983
There he is.

22:08.093 --> 22:09.493
- No, wait, Fonz. Wait a minute.
- What?

22:09.595 --> 22:11.825
Look, uh, don't hit him
or anything.

22:11.931 --> 22:13.831
I already had a long talk
with him.

22:13.933 --> 22:15.628
At this moment in my life,
I think that belting

22:15.734 --> 22:16.702
is better than talking.

22:16.802 --> 22:18.702
Well, maybe neither one is best.

22:18.804 --> 22:21.034
I think he's got to make up
his own mind on this.

22:21.140 --> 22:24.041
Hey, he can make up
his own mind.

22:24.143 --> 22:28.409
If he makes it wrong, I'm gonna
tie his eyebrows together.

22:28.514 --> 22:30.073
Hey, Chach, where are you?
Hey, there.

22:30.182 --> 22:32.014
Come on over here, look,
I got the weapons for you.

22:32.117 --> 22:33.949
Look at that. Hey, look at that.

22:34.053 --> 22:37.022
Your very own rumble chain,
what do you think of that?

22:37.122 --> 22:39.114
I oiled it for you, too, huh?

22:39.225 --> 22:40.886
You fight with chains?

22:40.993 --> 22:42.688
IGGY: Yeah, we got to teach
them Hornets, man,

22:42.795 --> 22:45.560
that they can't get away with
stepping on the Masher's foot.

22:45.664 --> 22:47.030
Right?

22:47.132 --> 22:49.362
You're rumbling over a foot?

22:49.468 --> 22:53.098
Yeah, we're gonna fight
for a lot of good reasons, man.

22:53.205 --> 22:55.105
Yeah, I heard.

22:55.207 --> 22:57.107
So just forget it.

22:57.209 --> 22:59.109
I don't want to be in your gang.

22:59.211 --> 23:01.145
(quietly):
What...?

23:03.749 --> 23:05.376
What?!

23:05.484 --> 23:06.975
Hey, kid, come over here.

23:07.086 --> 23:09.452
Nobody quits the Lords.

23:09.555 --> 23:10.784
Uh-uh.

23:10.889 --> 23:12.653
Not unless they want to go out
on a stretcher.

23:12.758 --> 23:14.055
So come on!

23:14.159 --> 23:16.594
You're gonna fight me?

23:16.695 --> 23:18.925
Kid...

23:19.031 --> 23:22.558
you got a lot of guts.

23:24.937 --> 23:28.839
Hey, kid, I'm gonna take you
and twist you around

23:28.941 --> 23:32.172
until I turn you inside out.

23:32.278 --> 23:34.769
- Oh, yeah? (chuckles)
- Yeah.

23:34.880 --> 23:36.348
Help?

23:37.383 --> 23:40.546
Okay, bucko,
you just put him down.

23:40.653 --> 23:42.280
You gonna mess with him,
you better be ready

23:42.388 --> 23:44.288
-to mess with me, too.
- Oh, wow.

23:44.390 --> 23:48.190
- That goes for me, too.
-(Iggy chuckles)

23:52.531 --> 23:53.692
Uh, well, look...

23:53.799 --> 23:56.860
Hey, uh... look, kid,

23:56.969 --> 23:58.869
nobody gotta
get hurt here, right?

23:58.971 --> 24:00.404
We don't mean to be here, right?

24:00.506 --> 24:02.633
Come on, let's get out of here.

24:02.741 --> 24:04.903
- And don't come back!
-(Richie chuckles)

24:05.010 --> 24:07.001
Chickens!

24:20.459 --> 24:21.517
You did the right thing, Chachi.

24:21.627 --> 24:22.526
CROWD (chanting):
Beat Mandeville!

24:22.628 --> 24:24.357
You're a good boy.

24:24.463 --> 24:25.453
Yeah, you did great.

24:25.564 --> 24:26.690
CROWD: Beat Mandeville!
Beat Mandeville!

24:26.799 --> 24:30.462
Fonz, uh, did you see that?
(chuckles)

24:30.569 --> 24:33.095
You guys were tigers.

24:34.573 --> 24:35.699
Let's go to a pep rally.

24:35.808 --> 24:36.968
- CROWD: Let's go, team...!
- Pep rally?

24:37.076 --> 24:38.304
Wait a minute.

24:38.410 --> 24:40.504
Telling me you're interested
in basketball?

24:40.612 --> 24:42.547
Who's talking baskets and balls?

24:42.648 --> 24:44.241
I'm talking cheerleaders.

24:44.350 --> 24:45.647
- Oh.
- Heyyy.

24:45.751 --> 24:47.810
Hey, wait for me!

24:47.920 --> 24:51.447
Cheerleaders-- wah, wah, wah.
(chuckles)

24:51.557 --> 24:52.683
FONZIE and RICHIE:
Wah, wah, wah.

24:52.791 --> 24:53.918
'Nah!

